This place was of legend for awhile until I finally made my way out.  It is a really neat place, known for cheap champagne and tons of tapas to offer.  The tapas are just great and the price is right!   Again, lack of tourists makes it an awesome experience.On the other hand, its so popular and crowded that it can be a bit of an annoyance.  People reach over your head, push you, and bump your drink often.  For people who hate being crowded (me), I'm not sure its a good choice.  Also, the neighborhood isn't very nice around it and it can be difficult to find.
